                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2673</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barclay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1278</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Britannic Majesty’s Chargé d’Affaires presents his compliments to the
                    Secretary of State and has the honour to inform him, by direction of his
                    Government, that the representative in London of the Polish National Committee
                    has been informed that His Majesty’s Government would view with serious
                    displeasure any military or other action of the Polish Government in East
                    Galicia or elsewhere of a nature to prejudge or forestall the decisions of the
                    Peace Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-15">November 15,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
